cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically in the context of autonomous vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a dash-cam for data capture suggests a focus on robotics and perception, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of manual labelling, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) in the context of privacy concerns related to the use of dash-cams.
